From Subject Words from the Chairman of Boeing on SSTO type stuff Yesterday I went to the Boeing shareholders It was a bit shorter than I Last year when the stock was first down they made a big presentation on the and other This year it was much more bare In any case I wanted to ask a question that the board of directors would hear and so I got there early and figured that If I didn't get to the mike maybe they would read mine off of a card and so I wrote it down and handed it After the meeting started Shrontz said that he would only answer written questions in order to be fair to the people in the overflow room that only had monitors Naturally I was So when question and answer time came I was suprised to find my question being read and Admittedly near the end of the ones that he Presumably getting there early and getting the question in early made all the So on to the The question was Is Boeing looking at anything BEYOND the high speed Civil Transport such as a commercial space launch system and if not how will Boeing compete with the reusable single stage to orbit technology presently being developed by Mcdonnell Douglass Well he read it without a hitch and without editing with impressed me then he answered it very quickly treating it as a two part question last part This is to the best of my recollection what he As far as single stage to orbit technology we think that we have a better answer in a two stage approach and we are talking to some of our customers about As far as commercialization that is a long ways The High speed Civil Transport is about as far out as our commercial planning goes at this So this tells me that Boeing still considers space to be a non commercial arena and for the most part this is true however it also tells me that they consider there to be enough money in building space launchers for them to persue work on their Now I do have a friend on the spacelifter program at Actually this is a mis nomer as there is no spacelifter contract for the work that this guy is doing however he is doing work in preparation of a proposal for space lifter He won't tell me what he is doing but maybe this is where the TSTO action is taking place at At the very minimum the chairman of the board of boeing said that they have an approach in mind and they are trying to do something with Anybody know anything further Is this really news Does this threaten further work on DC